# Companies

The Companies feature provides full lifecycle management of company records. Access is
role-gated: a **site admin** can see and manage all companies, while an **owner** can
only view and edit the companies they own. Companies cannot be deleted â€” they can only
be deactivated by setting their status to `inactive`.

---

## Access Control

| Role  | View list | Create | Edit | Deactivate |
| ----- | --------- | ------ | ---- | ---------- |
| Admin | All       | Yes    | Any  | Any        |
| Owner | Own only  | Yes    | Own  | Own        |
| Other | â€”         | â€”      | â€”    | â€”          |

Route `/admin/companies` is protected by `OwnerOrAdminRoute`, which redirects
unauthenticated or insufficiently-privileged users back to the home page.

Ownership enforcement for mutations is validated **server-side** in the controller:
the caller's `userId` is resolved to an `Owner` record and compared against the
target company's `ownerId` before any write proceeds.

---

## Data Model

Defined in `client/src/types/Entity.model.ts`.

### `Company`

| Field                | Type            | Notes                                      |
| -------------------- | --------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| `id`                 | `string` (UUID) |                                            |
| `name`               | `string`        | Required                                   |
| `registrationNumber` | `string`        | Required, unique, immutable after creation |
| `vatNumber`          | `string?`       |                                            |
| `status`             | `CompanyStatus` | `active` \| `inactive` \| `suspended`      |
| `description`        | `string?`       |                                            |
| `website`            | `string?`       |                                            |
| `phone`              | `string?`       |                                            |
| `email`              | `string?`       |                                            |
| `address`            | `string?`       |                                            |
| `city`               | `string?`       |                                            |
| `country`            | `string?`       | Country enum value                         |
| `logoUrl`            | `string?`       |                                            |
| `currency`           | `string?`       | e.g. `EUR`, `USD`                          |
| `foundedAt`          | `string?`       | ISO date string                            |
| `ownerId`            | `string`        | FK to `Owner`                              |
| `ownerName`          | `string?`       | Populated by server join                   |
| `createdAt`          | `string`        |                                            |
| `updatedAt`          | `string`        |                                            |

### `CompanyStatus`

```
active    â€” Company is operational
inactive  â€” Deactivated; no new employees or operations
suspended â€” Administratively suspended
```

---

## API

### Client (`client/src/api/companyApi.ts`)

| Method      | Endpoint                    | Description                                                    |
| ----------- | --------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `list()`    | `GET /companies`            | Lightweight `{ id, name }` list for dropdowns (admin only)     |
| `mine()`    | `GET /companies/mine`       | Companies the current user is linked to (as owner or employee) |
| `getAll()`  | `GET /companies/manage`     | Paginated full list with filters                               |
| `getById()` | `GET /companies/manage/:id` | Single company detail                                          |
| `create()`  | `POST /companies/manage`    | Create a new company                                           |
| `update()`  | `PUT /companies/manage/:id` | Update company fields or status                                |

### Server Routes (`server/src/routes/company.routes.ts`)

All routes require authentication (`authenticate` middleware).

| Method | Path                    | Guard         | Handler                |
| ------ | ----------------------- | ------------- | ---------------------- |
| GET    | `/companies`            | Admin only    | `listCompanies`        |
| GET    | `/companies/mine`       | Authenticated | `getMyCompanies`       |
| GET    | `/companies/manage`     | Authenticated | `listAllCompanies`     |
| GET    | `/companies/manage/:id` | Authenticated | `getCompany`           |
| POST   | `/companies/manage`     | Authenticated | `createCompanyHandler` |
| PUT    | `/companies/manage/:id` | Authenticated | `updateCompanyHandler` |

> No DELETE route exists by design â€” use `PUT` with `status: "inactive"` to deactivate.

### TanStack Query Hooks (`client/src/api/useCompany.tsx`)

| Hook                       | Purpose                                             |
| -------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| `useCompanies()`           | Admin dropdown list                                 |
| `useMyCompanies()`         | Current user's associated companies (dropdowns)     |
| `useAllCompanies(params?)` | Paginated manage list â€” used by the Companies page  |
| `useCompany(id)`           | Single company detail                               |
| `useCreateCompany()`       | Mutation; invalidates manage list + mine on success |
| `useUpdateCompany()`       | Mutation; invalidates manage list + detail + mine   |

---

## Components

### `Companies.tsx`

Main page component at `client/src/views/Companies/Companies.tsx`.

- Fetches data via `useAllCompanies` with debounced search (300 ms) and status filter.
- Displays an AG Grid table via the shared `DataGrid<Company>` component.
- **New Company** button is shown for admins and owners.
- Status filter dropdown always visible (all three statuses).
- Deactivation is confirmed with a browser `confirm()` dialog and executes
  `useUpdateCompany` with `{ status: "inactive" }`.

### `Companies.columns.tsx`

AG Grid column definitions.

| Column      | Field                | Notes                                                                          |
| ----------- | -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Name        | `name`               | Flex, min 180 px                                                               |
| Reg. Number | `registrationNumber` | Fixed 150 px                                                                   |
| VAT Number  | `vatNumber`          | Falls back to `â€”` if absent                                                    |
| City        | `city`               | Falls back to `â€”`                                                              |
| Country     | `country`            | Falls back to `â€”`                                                              |
| Status      | `status`             | Mantine `Badge`: green / gray / red                                            |
| Owner       | `ownerName`          | Resolved by server join; falls back to `â€”`                                     |
| Created     | `createdAt`          | Formatted as locale date string                                                |
| Actions     | â€”                    | Pinned right; Edit button + Deactivate button (disabled when already inactive) |

### `Modals/CreateCompanyModal.tsx`

Opens when clicking **New Company**.

- **Required fields**: Company name, Registration number, Owner.
- **Optional fields**: VAT number, Currency, Email, Phone, Website, Address, City,
  Country, Founded date, Description.
- **Owner field behaviour**:
  - Admin: searchable `Select` populated from `useOwners()`.
  - Owner: read-only text input pre-filled with their own name; `ownerId` is taken
    from `myOwner.id` automatically.
- Resets form on close or successful submission.

### `Modals/EditCompanyModal.tsx`

Opens when clicking the **Edit** action in the grid row.

- Pre-populates all fields from the selected company via a `useEffect` on `company` prop.
- **Editable fields**: Name, Status, VAT number, Currency, Email, Phone, Website,
  Address, City, Country, Description.
- `registrationNumber` is intentionally excluded â€” it cannot be changed after creation.
- Status can be changed to any value (`active`, `inactive`, `suspended`).
- Resets mutation state on close.

---

## Server-Side Logic (`server/src/services/companyService.ts`)

- **`listCompanies(query, ownerIds?)`** â€” Paginated query builder; when `ownerIds` is
  provided the result is automatically scoped to those owners (used to restrict non-admin
  callers to their own companies).
- **`getCompanyById(id)`** â€” Fetches a single company with owner + user join.
- **`createCompany(dto)`** â€” Validates `registrationNumber` uniqueness and that the
  target `Owner` record exists before inserting.
- **`updateCompany(id, dto)`** â€” Partial update; all fields optional. Status changes
  (including deactivation) are handled here.
- **`getOwnerIdForUser(userId)`** â€” Resolves a `userId` to an `Owner.id`, returning
  `null` if the user is not an owner. Used by the controller to enforce ownership.

### `getMyCompanies` resolution order

1. Check the JWT `roles` claim for `"admin"`.
2. If absent (old token), fall back to a DB lookup on `User.role`.
3. Admin â†’ return all companies.
4. Non-admin â†’ union of companies owned by the user's `Owner` record and the company of
   their `Employee` record.
